title: Bloomberg: Why Obama Is Wrong And Elizabeth Warren Is Right On Trade Bill Dispute
text:
Bloomberg: Why Obama Is Wrong And Elizabeth Warren Is Right On Trade Bill Dispute Bloomberg Updated: 41 minutes ago Legal experts back up Sen. Elizabeth Warren's claims that a new trade deal could undermine Dodd-Frank regulations. (Photo by Win McNamee/Getty Images) | Win McNamee via Getty Images reddit 
In her quarrel with President Barack Obama over trade legislation, Elizabeth Warren has got the law on her side. 
The Massachusetts senator has warned fellow Democrats that a fast-track trade bill now in Congress could undo U.S. laws such as the Dodd-Frank banking regulations later. A number of constitutional scholars and other legal experts say sheâ€™s right.
